This paper is about discriminative segmental models for speech recognition, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses different training approaches and loss functions, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and statistical learning (cs.SD). Additionally, the use of deep neural networks for feature extraction and classification is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and signal processing (cs.SI).
